          <long_desc isprivate="0">
            <commentid>27756</commentid>
            <who name="Daniel Wagner">daniel.wagner</who>
            <bug_when>2011-12-01 17:26:39 +0100</bug_when>
            <thetext>We removed around 60 browser engine checks from the framework classes and replaced them with feature checks. There are still 40 open tasks where more work is necessary to determine if feature detection is applicable or if we can at least restrict workarounds to specific browser version.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
          <long_desc isprivate="0">
            <commentid>29051</commentid>
            <who name="Daniel Wagner">daniel.wagner</who>
            <bug_when>2012-04-03 17:48:12 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>For IE-specific code that we can&#39;t switch to feature detection, we need to make sure the right environment keys are queried. For example, IE9 will often behave like one of the legacy versions when in compatibility mode. In that case, we need to check the document mode instead of the browser/engine version.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
